1
00:00:00,289 --> 00:00:01,120
Hello world,

2
00:00:01,250 --> 00:00:02,240
my name is David Malan,

3
00:00:02,289 --> 00:00:03,490
and I teach CS50,

4
00:00:03,609 --> 00:00:06,909
a free introduction to the intellectual enterprises of computer science

5
00:00:07,010 --> 00:00:08,229
and the art of programming

6
00:00:08,409 --> 00:00:10,390
with and without artificial intelligence,

7
00:00:10,569 --> 00:00:13,350
freely available at cs50.edx.org.

8
00:00:13,630 --> 00:00:16,610
Each year we host an event at Harvard University called CS50

9
00:00:16,610 --> 00:00:19,649
Puzzle Day during which students tackle a packet of puzzles,

10
00:00:19,750 --> 00:00:21,170
logic problems of sorts,

11
00:00:21,299 --> 00:00:22,979
for fun and fabulous prizes.

12
00:00:23,139 --> 00:00:26,409
And each year we also hold an event called CS50x Puzzle Day,

13
00:00:26,540 --> 00:00:29,420
which is an online adaptation of the same open to

14
00:00:29,420 --> 00:00:32,319
everyone around the world whether taking CS50 or not.

15
00:00:32,619 --> 00:00:35,729
No prior computer science or programming experience is required.

16
00:00:35,939 --> 00:00:38,380
You're encouraged to form a team of size 2, 3,

17
00:00:38,389 --> 00:00:38,970
or 4,

18
00:00:39,259 --> 00:00:40,720
or you can participate on your own,

19
00:00:41,020 --> 00:00:42,459
and teachers are welcome to host their

20
00:00:42,590 --> 00:00:43,970
own version during class.

21
00:00:44,229 --> 00:00:45,650
Now if you need help forming a team,

22
00:00:45,750 --> 00:00:47,029
no matter where you are in the world,

23
00:00:47,189 --> 00:00:49,939
reach out to others via any of CS50's communities.

24
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:53,459
You're welcome to collaborate on the puzzles when the time comes via WhatsApp,

25
00:00:53,599 --> 00:00:53,990
Zoom,

26
00:00:53,990 --> 00:00:55,330
or any other platform.

27
00:00:55,549 --> 00:00:57,830
To participate in CS50x puzzle day,

28
00:00:58,496 --> 00:01:01,486
register at cs50.ly/register.

29
00:01:02,110 --> 00:01:02,650
This

30
00:01:02,790 --> 00:01:03,750
is CS50.